source.ce9c5813:
This notebook is to test pycaret installation in Kaggle kernel **without** internet access, assuming that you would need to install pycaret but you would not be allowed to use 'pip install' command for package installation.

Pycaret version "2.3.2" is specified, which is the latest version at the moment I am working on this notebook.

Hereafter is the link to the notebook with internet access version.
https://www.kaggle.com/yuichihiguchi/install-pycaret-with-internet?scriptVersionId=67923215
